content.description:
Start on the far left side of the boulder on a jug just right of the sickly tree. Make some moves to the start hold on Blang and take the path of least resistance right and trending up until the arete. Top out over the arete.

This route is #9 on Boulder 2: Warm-up Boulder in the Warm-up Boulders in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: The start is on the far left side of the Warm-up Boulder just right of the sickly tree.

content.description: Stand-start and follow good crimpers and finger jugs to a thinner finish (you need to find the good holds.)
content.location: The obvious arete on the Warm-Up Boulder

content.description: Sit-start on low holds and make a difficult sit-start move (kinda tweaky.)  Follow good holds up the arete to the top.
content.location: The obvious arete on the Warm-Up boulder.

content.description:
Step up to a good horizontal just right of the ledge.  Follows pockets to a straight forward topout just left of the mini roof.

This route is # 17 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack & Keenan guidebook.

Stand start using a thin ledge a few feet right of the arete on the Warm-Up boulder. Stand up on the good ledge for your feet following more thin ledges with your hands. Find some sort of feet and go up through pockets to the top out.
content.location: On the Warm-Up boulder just right of the arete.

content.description: Sit start on a jug a few feet left of the arete on the Warm-Up boulder. Make your way up through thin but good holds until you get to a good pocket and top out.
content.location: The first problem left of the arete on the Warm-Up boulder

content.description:
Stand Start. Start on a pocket on the left and some horizontals to the left of the arete. Make your way through some long moves to good jugs to the top.

This route is # 10 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook.
content.location: Route just to the left of the right arete on the river side of the Beginners Face.

content.description: Start standing using good pockets below the good ledge hold. Move up and follow the flake finding holds around it to the  top out.
content.location: On the Warm-Up boulder, the second problem to the left of the arete.

content.description:
Start on two high pockets.  Step up to more pockets and good horizontals, leading to a topout just right of the roof.

This route is # 13 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack & Keenan guidebook.
content.location: Begins below the right side of the roof.

content.description:
Start on a pocket and a two finger pinch.  Use pockets and a few horizontals to reach a slightly plant-y topout.

This route is # 11 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack & Keenan guidebook.
content.location: Begins a few feet right of the small talus.

content.description: Sit start below arete. Follow arete to the top. Bad landing. Highball.
content.location: Downhill through a narrow corridor opposite the Warm-Up arete. This arete is on your left as your exit the corridor.

content.description:
Start standing using the same giant pocket as Blang and move up to the lip of the face just right of the tree. Instead of topping out there like Blang does, move right along the lip of the face to the arete. Top out over the arete.

This route is #8a on Boulder 2: Warm-up Boulder in the Warm-up Boulders in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: Start on the giant pocket just under the tree at the top of the middle of the Boulder.

content.description:
Two move wonder that would be super fun if it was longer. On the opposite side of the corridor from Censor.

Problem 22 in the Falcon guidebook by Brayack and Keenan.
content.location: Locate Warm-Up Arete. Turnaround and you will see a short, narrow corridor. This is the obvious problem on the boulder forming the right side of the corridor. Across from it is Censor, on the taller wall.

content.description:
Start on a horizontal and a right facing sidepull.  Follow more horizontals and pockets to another easy topout.

This route is # 16 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack & Keenan guidebook.
content.location: Start just left of the large tree, between the two roofs on the wall.

content.description:
Stand Start, High Ball. Start on some pockets and move up to a noticeable horizontal. Follow the line of pockets and crimps to the top staying just to the right of the arete.

This route is # 19 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook.
content.location: First route climbers right of the left arete on the river face on the Beginners Face boulder. From Kaleidoscope, go down the path between the 2 boulders and the face will be to your left.

content.description: Start as far back as you can on jugs and follow the flake system out the roof to the lip.  Make a long move and finish with a topout.  Not dabbing is definitely one of the cruxes.
content.location: As you are coming down the main trail into the area, you will a roof to your left at about knee height.  If you stoop down, you'll see this is actually a boulder problem.

content.description:
Stand Start. To get established at the start, stand on a talus to find your starting holds. Reach up through good holds to an easy topout. Beware the thorn bush this route gets its name from, which is probably the only reason this route gets its V0 grade.

This route is # 12 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook.
content.location: 10 feet left of the right arete on the face. Look for the starting talus that you stand on.

content.description:
Stand Start. Start on some pockets under the left side of the Boulder roof.  Find and follow the jugs and top out to the left of the Boulder roof.

This route is # 15 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook.
content.location: Route that goes under the left side of the noticeable Boulder roof middle right of the wall.

content.description:
Stand Start. Follow the pockets up to the middle of the Boulder roof and top out through the middle of the roof.

This problem is # 14 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook.
content.location: Route that goes through the middle of the noticeable Boulder roof in the middle-right of the Beginners Face.

climbs.name: Grandma Got Run Over on a Rock

content.description:
Stand Start, High Ball. Start on a jug and work through the horizontals passed a sidepull and through some pockets on a slabby face to an easy topout.

This problem is  # 18 on Boulder 3: Beginners Face in the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook.
content.location: Second route climbers right of the left arete on the river face on the beginners face boulder. 8 feet to right of How to Cripple Grandma. Look for the noticeable vertical crack at the bottom of the rock and go straight up from there.

content.description:
A tallish problem with a sketchy boulder (containing the problem Kaleidoscope) at your back as you climb.

Start on a good horizontal and a foot jug, and stand up to a suspect left facing flake. Work your feet up to gain the two finger pocket a couple feet below the top edge. Aim for the apex of the bulge on the lip and go for it. The top out is sketchy and that boulder you want to grab is pretty wobbly. I used it anyway.

This is problem 23 in the "Warm-Up Boulders" at Roadside, in the Falcon Guide by Brayack and Keenan.
content.protection: A pad and a spotter for the top-out.
content.location: In the corridor that is behind you if you are facing the Warm Up Arete. Left side of the corridor is Censor. To your right is the shorter, burlier route Kaleidoscope.

content.description:
Stand start. Start on the triangular jug and follow a slabby path up finishing by topping out just right of the tree (as seen in photo).

This route is #8 on Boulder 2: Warm-up Boulder in the Warm-up Boulders in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: Just under the tree at the top of the middle of the Boulder.

content.description:
Start the same as Bizzaro, but make unique moves on a two small crimps to get your body around the lip and onto the slab, various betas possible. Avoid the right arete while ascending the slab.

This route is #2a on Boulder 2 in the Warm-Up Boulder area of the Brayack and Keenan falcon guidebook, originally published as V5.
content.location: This climbs the slab over Bizzaro at the Warm-Up Boulders. It is one of the first visible boulders to your right when approaching from the parking lot.

content.description: Sit-start compression style on the left side of the roof.  (The back block is off.)  Do some compression moves out the roof; do some kungfu and finish up the arete.  Classic.
content.location: This trash-compactor roof is an obvious feature in the warm-up area.  It sits just to the right of the Warm-Up boulder proper.

content.description: Stand start with hands on an obvious ledge. Go up and slightly left to a good horizontal and work the foot beta to get to the top out.
content.location:
The first boulder problem on the Warm-Up boulder (going right to left). The start is in the middle of the vertical (slightly slabby) face of the Warm-Up Boulder, slightly to the left of a small tree.

From the closest parking area, the first routes you'll come to is a cave on your left. This is the Helicopter Boulder. Continuing down the trail, head right from Helicopter. In this same area, the overhung refrigerator block holds the route Bizzaro. Just to the left of this block is the face this problem is on.
